    <title>Installing from a .deb file (Debian, Ubuntu, Derivatives)</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>To install D++ on a system from .deb using dpkg (as root):</para>
<para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal">apt<sp/>install<sp/>wget</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">wget<sp/>-O<sp/>dpp.deb<sp/>https://dl.dpp.dev/</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">dpkg<sp/>-i<sp/>dpp.deb</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>This will do the following three things:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Install <computeroutput>wget</computeroutput></para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Use <computeroutput>wget</computeroutput> to download the latest release of D++ to <computeroutput>dpp.deb</computeroutput></para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Install <computeroutput>dpp.deb</computeroutput> to /usr</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>You will now be able to use D++ by including its library on the command line:</para>
<para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal">g++<sp/>mybot.cpp<sp/>-o<sp/>mybot<sp/>-ldpp</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting> </para>
    </detaileddescription>
